&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-3f24567e-7fff-a70b-8d8e-8646326c8549&quot; style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;The given word&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt; &amp;#39;engulfed&amp;#39; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;means&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;(of a natural force) sweep over (something) so as to surround or cover it completely.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&lt;img alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;https://storage.googleapis.com/tb-img/production/20/08/428.png&quot; style=&quot;width: 35px; height: 35px; float: left;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;margin-left: 40px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em style=&quot;&quot;&gt;​Let&amp;#39;s have a look at the meanings of the given words:&lt;/em&gt;

	&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Covered-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;  &quot;&gt;put something on top of or in front of (something) in order to protect or conceal it.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Escaped-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;  &quot;&gt;having broken free from confinement or control.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Enclosed-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;  &quot;&gt;surrounded or closed off on all sides.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&lt;i style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Surrounded-&amp;nbsp;&lt;/i&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;  &quot;&gt;be all round (someone or something).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li style=&quot;&quot;&gt;The most appropriate antonym&amp;nbsp;of the given options is&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;escaped&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&amp;nbsp;i.e 2nd&amp;nbsp;option.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Jubilation&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The most appropriate &lt;strong&gt;synonym&lt;/strong&gt; of the given word &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Exultation&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39; is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;Jubilation&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Exultation&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;a feeling of triumphant elation or jubilation; rejoicing. (विजयी अभिलाषा या उल्लास की भावना; आनन्द)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;She laughs in &lt;strong&gt;exultation&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Jubilation&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;great happiness because of a success. (सफलता प्राप्ति पर) हर्षोल्लास, आनंदोत्&amp;zwj;सव
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;There was much &lt;strong&gt;jubilation&lt;/strong&gt; among the garrison at this outcome of the long-expected and dreaded attack.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;Correct Answer:&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Jubilation.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of other words:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Depression&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;a feeling of unhappiness that lasts for a long time. Depression can be a medical condition and may have physical signs, for example being unable to sleep, etc.. विषाद का भाव, अवसाद (यह देर तक रहता है और कभी-कभी अनिद्रा आदि के रूप में प्रकट होता है)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Agitation&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;a state of anxiety or nervous excitement. (चिंता या घबराहट की स्थिति)&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Irritation&lt;/strong&gt;:&amp;nbsp;the state of feeling annoyed, impatient, or slightly angry. (नाराज़, अधीर, या थोड़ा गुस्सा महसूस करने की स्थिति)&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

The correct answer is-&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Praise&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;given word&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;and the&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;correct answer.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Invective&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;criticism that is very forceful, unkind, and often rude (आलोचना जो बहुत ही ज़बरदस्त, निर्दयी और अक्सर असभ्य होती है)&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(48, 51, 54); font-variant-ligatures: no-common-ligatures; letter-spacing: 0.2px;&quot;&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(48, 51, 54); font-variant-ligatures: no-common-ligatures; letter-spacing: 0.2px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;invective&lt;/strong&gt; here is not against pleasure as such.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Praise&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;to express admiration or approval of the achievements or characteristics of a person or thing (किसी व्यक्ति या चीज़ की उपलब्धियों या विशेषताओं की प्रशंसा या अनुमोदन व्यक्त करने के लिए)&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(32, 33, 36);&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;My parents always &lt;strong&gt;praised&lt;/strong&gt; me when I did well at school.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
		&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Hence, the word&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Praise&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;is the most appropriate antonym for&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Invective.&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul style=&quot;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s explore the meaning of other options&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Abuse&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;to use something for the wrong purpose in a way that is harmful or morally wrong (गलत उद्देश्य के लिए किसी चीज का उपयोग इस तरह से करना जो हानिकारक या नैतिक रूप से गलत हो)&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;I never expected that he would &lt;strong&gt;abuse&lt;/strong&gt; the trust I placed in him.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Insults&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;an offensive remark or action (एक आपत्तिजनक टिप्पणी या कार्रवाई)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;She made several &lt;strong&gt;insults&lt;/strong&gt; about my appearance&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;Swear Words&lt;/span&gt;:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;a rude or offensive word&amp;nbsp;(एक अशिष्ट या आपत्तिजनक शब्द)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700;&quot;&gt;Example:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;All &lt;strong&gt;swear words&lt;/strong&gt;, even mild ones such as &amp;quot;damn&amp;quot;,, were deleted from the text.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Option 1&amp;#39; i.e. &amp;#39;Zoophilous&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Being &amp;#39;attracted to or caused by animals&amp;#39; is referred to as &amp;#39;Zoophilous&amp;#39; in English. (पशु प्रेमी).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;Example: Zoophilous plants rely on animals for pollination.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Therefore, the correct answer is- &amp;#39;Zoophilous&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul dir=&quot;ltr&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Yawning&amp;#39;, as previously discussed, refers to a reflex consisting of the simultaneous inhalation of air and the stretching of the eardrums, followed by an exhalation of breath. (जम्भाई).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Zirconium&amp;#39;, as previously discussed, is a chemical element with the symbol Zr and atomic number 40. (ज़िरकोनियम).&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li role=&quot;presentation&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;Yttrium&amp;#39;, as previously discussed, is a chemical element with the symbol &amp;lsquo;Y&amp;rsquo;. It is a rare earth metal that is often used in various electronics and lasers. (यट्रियम).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;option 3 i.e. country.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Looking at the meaning of the given sentence we find that:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The phrase to &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;the order to stay in one&amp;#39;s own bailiwick&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; means the person should be &lt;em&gt;confined to one&amp;#39;s own country.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
