	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Let&amp;#39;s look at the meaning of the word&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;bailiwick&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;​Bailiwick&lt;/strong&gt;: I&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;s usually the area of&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); &quot; title=&quot;Jurisdiction&quot;&gt;jurisdiction&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;of a&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); &quot; title=&quot;Bailiff&quot;&gt;bailiff&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;, and once also applied to territories.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot; &quot;&gt;​Thus from the above options, we find that the word country is the most appropriate.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Clearly, &lt;strong&gt;option 3&lt;/strong&gt; is correct.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span id=&quot;docs-internal-guid-e8df05ce-7fff-44c9-59e4-25f23f380f8b&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;  font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;The correct answer is -&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Blurb&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;  font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; vertical-align: baseline; white-space: pre-wrap;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Blurb&amp;#39; &lt;/strong&gt;is a &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;verb&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; which means &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;a short description of a book, film or other product written for promotional purposes&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Example: This is the first time I have &lt;strong&gt;blurbed&lt;/strong&gt; a whole line of books&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Hence &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;A short piece of writing that praises and promotes something&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; is &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Blurb&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;table border=&quot;1&quot; cellpadding=&quot;1&quot; cellspacing=&quot;1&quot; style=&quot;width:500px;&quot;&gt;
	&lt;tbody&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width: 80px; height: 5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WORDS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td style=&quot;width: 166px; height: 5px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;MEANING&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Blonde&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;&lt;em&gt;(a person) with fair or yellow hair&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bohemian&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;&lt;em&gt;a native or inhabitant of Bohemia (now the western part of the Czech Republic)&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
		&lt;tr&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bookworm&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
			&lt;td&gt;&lt;em&gt;a person who enjoys reading&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
		&lt;/tr&gt;
	&lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;synonyms &lt;/strong&gt;of the word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Blurb&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; are &lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;packaging, endorsement, promotional, material, endorsement, promotion, publicity&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;antonyms&lt;/strong&gt; of the word &lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;Blurb&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt; are&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;disapproval, disagreement, demotion, discouragement&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Notorious&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;The one word substitution for the given group of words is :&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Let us explore the given options and know their meanings:
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Notorious&lt;/strong&gt; means well-known for something bad.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Burglar&lt;/strong&gt; means&amp;nbsp;a person who illegally enters buildings and steals things.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Thief &lt;/strong&gt;means&amp;nbsp;a person who steals things from another person.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;Idiot &lt;/strong&gt;means&amp;nbsp;a foolish or stupid person.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Therefore, from the meanings,&amp;nbsp;it is clear that the most appropriate word for the given group of words is&lt;strong&gt; &amp;#39;Notorious&amp;#39;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;Hence, the correct answer is&lt;strong&gt; option 1.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;#39;advocate&amp;#39;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Endorse&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;means&amp;nbsp;to&amp;nbsp;declare one&amp;#39;s public approval or support of. (पृष्ठांकन करना,&amp;nbsp;समर्थन करना,&amp;nbsp;पुष्टि करना)

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Example:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;The National Executive is expected to &lt;strong&gt;endorse &lt;/strong&gt;these recommendations.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The meaning of the given options are as follows -&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;criticize&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;indicate the faults of (someone or something) in a disapproving way. (निन्दा करना,&amp;nbsp;दोष निकालना)&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;You were quite right to &lt;strong&gt;criticize &lt;/strong&gt;him.&lt;/em&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;advocate&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;publicly recommend or support. (वकालत करना,समर्थन करना)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&amp;nbsp;Heart disease specialists &lt;strong&gt;advocate &lt;/strong&gt;a diet low in cholesterol.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;disapprove&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;have or express an unfavourable opinion. (ठुकरा देना,अस्वीकार करना)
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;​&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Most people &lt;strong&gt;disapprove &lt;/strong&gt;of such violent tactics.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;censure&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;-&amp;nbsp;express severe disapproval of (someone or something), especially in a formal statement.&amp;nbsp;(निन्दा करना,अपराधी ठहराना)&amp;nbsp;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;Example:&lt;/span&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;Public &lt;strong&gt;censure &lt;/strong&gt;should be reserved largely for those who pulled the trigger.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;From the above meanings it is evident that&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;advocate&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is the correct synonym for the word&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;endorse&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Hence,&amp;nbsp;&lt;strong&gt;option 2&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;is the correct answer.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;failed spectacularly&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;strong&gt;G&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;o down in flames&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&amp;#39; is an idiom that means &lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;u&gt;&lt;em&gt;to fail suddenly and spectacularly, thereby ruining its prospects&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;For example, &lt;em&gt;&amp;#39;Despite all the promotions, the major summer release by Akshay Kumar &lt;strong&gt;went down in flames&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;mdash;hardly anyone went to see it.&amp;#39;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thus, the idiom &amp;#39;went down in flames&amp;#39; in the given sentence means&amp;nbsp;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 700; &quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;failed spectacularly&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&amp;#39;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;So, the correct answer is &lt;strong&gt;Option 3&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

